						LINEAR DISCRIMINANT ANALYSIS (LDA)
Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) is a supervised machine learning algorithm used mainly for classification and dimensionality reduction. It works by finding a linear combination of features that best separates two or more classes. Unlike algorithms that only classify data, LDA also reduces the number of input features while preserving the information that distinguishes different classes. This helps improve model performance, reduce computation time, and avoid overfitting. LDA is widely used in face recognition, medical diagnosis, speech recognition, and pattern classification.
