 Binary Classification      Multi-class Classification

2.1 Binary LDA
Definition
Binary Linear Discriminant Analysis is used when the dataset contains only two classes. The algorithm finds the best linear boundary that separates the two classes by maximizing the distance between class means while minimizing the variation within each class. It is simple, fast, and effective for binary classification problems.
