Examples
	• Spam or Not Spam 
	• Disease Positive or Negative 
	• Loan Approved or Rejected 
	• Pass or Fail 

2.2 Multi-class LDA
Definition
Multi-class Linear Discriminant Analysis is used when the dataset contains more than two classes. It identifies multiple discriminant directions that maximize the separation among all classes simultaneously. This allows the algorithm to classify observations into one of several categories while reducing the dimensionality of the data.
