Number of Classes	Two	More than Two
Decision Boundary	Single Linear Boundary	Multiple Linear Boundaries
Complexity	Low	Moderate
Example	Spam Detection	Flower Species Classification

LDA vs PCA
Feature	LDA	PCA
Learning Type	Supervised	Unsupervised
Uses Class Labels	Yes	No
Goal	Maximize class separation	Maximize data variance
Best Used For	Classification	Dimensionality Reduction
Output	Discriminant Components	Principal Components

Summary
Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for both classification and dimensionality reduction. It identifies the best linear combinations of features that maximize the separation between different classes while minimizing variation within the same class. LDA is commonly applied in binary and multi-class classification problems and performs well when the data follows a normal distribution with similar class covariances. Because of its simplicity, efficiency, and ability to improve classification performance, LDA is widely used in face recognition, healthcare, speech recognition, and pattern recognition.
